cs.GT, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.PL 

This paper deals with the complexity of solving multi-mean-payoff and multi-energy games, which are types of games with applications in the synthesis of resource-bounded processes. The paper involves mathematical analysis and algorithmic complexity, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on game theory and algorithmic complexity makes cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) the most likely category. The paper also involves logic and decision-making, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of data structures and algorithms could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
